<section>
	<h1>Cubic Bezier</h1>

	<div class="copy-block">
		<p>Defined by four points on a curve.</p>
		<p>I'm not a mathematician, so this will be very high level.</p>
	</div>

	<div class="side-by-side-block">
		<div class="copy-block copy-block--auto-width">
			<p>X axis represents the animation duration.</p>
			<p>Y axis represents the progression/speed of the animation.</p>
			<p>The grey lines influence line between A & B the curves. The ball at the end is set with X/Y coordinates.</p>
		</div>

		<%= image_tag('cubic.png') %>

	</div>

	<div class="code-block">
		<p>cubic-bezier(</p>
		<p class="indent" data-indent="1">X axis of left ball,</p>
		<p class="indent" data-indent="1">Y axis of left ball,</p>
		<p class="indent" data-indent="1">X axis of right ball,</p>
		<p class="indent" data-indent="1">Y axis of right ball,</p>
		<p>)</p>
		<p>cubic-bezier(0.12, 0.57, 0.63, 0.21);</p>
	</div>

	<div class="copy-block">
		<p>Y values can go below 0 and above 1, but X must stay between 0 and 1.</p>
		<p>You animation can move backwards ov overextend, but we can't control time.</p>
	</div>

